data.chText: 种类
data.enText: variety

data.chText: 一系列
data.enText: a variety of things of a particular type

data.chText: 这家酒店提供各种各样的设施。
data.enText: The hotel offers a wide range of facilities.

data.chText: 这里有给孩子们提供的各种活动。
data.enText: There is a full range of activities for children.

data.chText: 界限
data.enText: limits

data.chText: （变动或浮动的）范围，界限，区间
data.enText: the limits between which sth varies

data.chText: 大多数学生都是在17至20岁的年龄范围内。
data.enText: Most of the students are in the 17-20 age range.

data.chText: 将会有0到3个百分点的增长幅度。
data.enText: There will be an increase in the range of 0 to 3 per cent.

data.chText: 在我们的价格范围以内，很难找到房子。
data.enText: It's difficult to find a house in our price range (= that we can afford) .

data.chText: 这超出了他的阅历。
data.enText: This was outside the range of his experience .

data.chText: 产品
data.enText: of products

data.chText: 类；种
data.enText: a set of products of a particular type

data.chText: 我们的新的头发产品系列
data.enText: our new range of hair products

data.chText: 距离
data.enText: distance

data.chText: 视觉（或听觉）范围
data.enText: the distance over which sth can be seen or heard

data.chText: 这孩子已经走出了她的视线。
data.enText: The child was now out of her range of vision (= not near enough for her to see) .

data.chText: 射程；射击距离
data.enText: the distance over which a gun or other weapon can hit things

data.chText: 这些导弹的射程为300英里。
data.enText: These missiles have a range of 300 miles.

data.chText: （车辆）加一次油可行的路程
data.enText: the distance that a vehicle will travel before it needs more fuel

data.chText: 山
data.enText: of mountains

data.chText: 山脉
data.enText: a line or group of mountains or hills

data.chText: 雄伟的阿尔卑斯山脉
data.enText: the great mountain range of the Alps

data.chText: 射击
data.enText: for shooting

data.chText: 靶场；射击场；炸弹试验场
data.enText: an area of land where people can practise shooting or where bombs, etc. can be tested

data.chText: 射击场
data.enText: a shooting range

data.chText: 炉子
data.enText: oven

data.chText: （尤指旧时的）炉灶
data.enText: a large piece of equipment that can burn various fuels and is kept hot all the time, used for cooking, especially in the past

data.chText: 把肉放在炉灶上用文火炖着。
data.enText: Cook the meat on a low heat on top of the range.

data.chText: 乳牛
data.enText: for cows

data.chText: 牧场；乳牛场
data.enText: a large open area for keeping cows, etc.
in/within range (of sth)

data.chText: 在可及的范围内；在视觉（或听觉）范围内
data.enText: near enough to be reached, seen or heard

data.chText: 他看见谁，就对谁吼叫。
data.enText: He shouted angrily at anyone within range.
out of range (of sth)

data.chText: 超出…的范围；在视觉（或听觉）范围之外
data.enText: too far away to be reached, seen or heard

data.chText: 这只猫离孩子们远远的。
data.enText: The cat stayed well out of range of the children.

data.chText: 变化
data.enText: vary

data.chText: （在一定的范围内）变化，变动
data.enText: to vary between two particular amounts, sizes, etc., including others between them

data.chText: 尺寸 / 长度 / 价格在A到B间变动
data.enText: to range in size/length/price from A to B

data.chText: 估计损失在100万到500万元之间。
data.enText: Estimates of the damage range between $1 million and $5 million.

data.chText: 住宿条件从经济旅馆至豪华宾馆不等。
data.enText: Accommodation ranges from tourist class to luxury hotels.

data.chText: 包括（从…到…）之间的各类事物
data.enText: to include a variety of different things in addition to those mentioned

data.chText: 她做过许多不同的工作，从厨师到游泳教练。
data.enText: She has had a number of different jobs, ranging from chef to swimming instructor.

data.chText: 谈话所涉及的范围很广。
data.enText: The conversation ranged widely (= covered a lot of different topics) .

data.chText: 安排
data.enText: arrange

data.chText: （按一定位置或顺序）排列，排序
data.enText: to arrange people or things in a particular position or order

data.chText: 代表依次在桌子周围就座。
data.enText: The delegates ranged themselves around the table.

data.chText: 旁观者排列在整个游行路线的两侧。
data.enText: Spectators were ranged along the whole route of the procession.

data.chText: 徘徊
data.enText: move around

data.chText: 徘徊；漫步；四处移动
data.enText: to move around an area

data.chText: 他四处漫步，寻找绘画的灵感。
data.enText: He ranges far and wide in search of inspiration for his paintings.

data.chText: 她的目光在屋子里来回扫视。
data.enText: Her eyes ranged the room.
range yourself/sb against/with sb/sth

data.chText: （使）结伙反对 / 支持…
data.enText: to join with other people to oppose or support sb/sth

data.chText: 一家人好像在合伙对付他。
data.enText: The whole family seemed ranged against him.
range over sth

data.chText: 涉及；包括
data.enText: to include a variety of different subjects

data.chText: 他的讲座涉及许多话题。
data.enText: His lecture ranged over a number of topics.

means: 包括(从…到…)之间的各类事物

ex.chText: 这款游戏适合学龄前儿童。
ex.enText: This game is suitable for children in the pre-school age range.

ex.chText: 那家公司多数员工的薪水在3000元到5000元之间。
ex.enText: Most workers in that company earn a salary in the range of 3000 yuan to 4000 yuan.
This coat is out of my price range.

ex.chText: 她阅读的书籍涉及诸多学科。
ex.enText: Her reading covers a wide range of subjects.

synonyms.bx: 指数、量、年龄等的范围，常后接具体的上下限额。

ex.chText: 实际上，他是个金融领域的投机者。
ex.enText: In fact, he is an adventurer in the financial field.

ex.chText: 他在自己的领域里已经大名鼎鼎了。
ex.enText: He has become very famous in his own field.
She works in the field of environmental protection.
Who is the expert in that field?

ex.chText: 警方首先要界定调查范围。
ex.enText: The police had to first define the scope of the investigation.

ex.chText: 对后殖民主义问题的讨论不在本书范围之内。
ex.enText: A discussion of post-colonial issues is beyond the scope of this book.

synonyms.bx: 指学科、活动、书籍等的范围，也指不同的活动圈子。

data.enText: in/within range (of sth)

data.chText: 在可及的范围内；在视觉（或听觉）范围内
data.enText: near enough to be reached, seen or heard

data.chText: 他看见谁，就对谁吼叫。
data.enText: He shouted angrily at anyone within range.

data.chText: 超出…的范围；在视觉（或听觉）范围之外
data.enText: too far away to be reached, seen or heard

data.chText: 这只猫离孩子们远远的。
data.enText: The cat stayed well out of range of the children.

data.enText: to join with other people to oppose or support sb/sth

data.chText: 一家人好像在合伙对付他。
data.enText: The whole family seemed ranged against him.
range over sth

data.chText: 涉及；包括
data.enText: to include a variety of different subjects

data.chText: 他的讲座涉及许多话题。
data.enText: His lecture ranged over a number of topics.

tr: a place for shooting (firing or driving) projectiles of various kinds
example: the army maintains a missile range in the desert
any good golf club will have a range where you can practice

tr: a kitchen appliance used for cooking food
example: dinner was already on the stove

tr: an area in which something acts or operates or has power or control: "the range of a supersonic jet"
example: a piano has a greater range than the human voice
the ambit of municipal legislation
within the compass of this article
within the scope of an investigation
outside the reach of the law
in the political orbit of a world power
within the compass of education

tr: (mathematics) the set of values of the dependent variable for which a function is defined
example: the image of f(x) = x^2 is the set of all non-negative real numbers if the domain of the function is the set of all real numbers

tr: a variety of different things or activities
example: he answered a range of questions
he was impressed by the range and diversity of the collection

tr: the limits within which something can be effective
example: range of motion
he was beyond the reach of their fire

tr: a large tract of grassy open land on which livestock can graze
example: they used to drive the cattle across the open range every spring
he dreamed of a home on the range

tr: a series of hills or mountains
example: the valley was between two ranges of hills
the plains lay just beyond the mountain range

tr: assign a rank or rating to
example: how would you rank these students?
The restaurant is rated highly in the food guide
range the animals in the prairie

tr: lay out orderly or logically in a line or as if in a line
example: lay out the clothes
lay out the arguments

tr: feed as in a meadow or pasture
example: the herd was grazing

tr: move about aimlessly or without any destination, often in search of food or employment
example: The gypsies roamed the woods
roving vagabonds
the wandering Jew
The cattle roam across the prairie
the laborers drift from one town to the next
They rolled from town to town
The plants straddle the entire state

tr: change or be different within limits
example: Estimates for the losses in the earthquake range as high as $2 billion
Interest rates run from 5 to 10 percent
The instruments ranged from tuba to cymbals
My students range from very bright to dull

tr: be capable of projecting over a certain distance, as of a gun
example: This gun ranges over two miles

value.def: A range of things is a number of different things of the same general kind.

example.ex: A wide range of colours and patterns are available...
example.tran: 各种颜色和样式都有。

example.ex: The two men discussed a range of issues...
example.tran: 那两个人讨论了一系列问题。

example.ex: The range includes chests of drawers, tables and wardrobes.
example.tran: 该系列包括五斗柜、桌子和衣橱。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: A range is the complete group that is included between two points on a scale of measurement or quality.

example.ex: The average age range is between 35 and 55.
example.tran: 平均年龄在35岁到55岁之间。

example.ex: ...properties available in the price range they are looking for.
example.tran: 在他们寻求的价格范围内的房产

example.ex: ...top-of-the-range products for which people are prepared to pay a little bit more.
example.tran: 人们愿意多花一点钱购买的高档产品

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft n N

value.def: The range of something is the maximum area in which it can reach things or detect things.

example.ex: The 120mm mortar has a range of 18,000 yards...
example.tran: 口径为120毫米的迫击炮的射程是1.8万码。

example.ex: The trees on the mountains within my range of vision had all been felled...
example.tran: 山上我视野范围内的树木都被砍倒了。

example.ex: Tactical nuclear weapons have shorter ranges.
example.tran: 战术核武器的威力范围较小。

value.def: If things range between two points or range from one point to another, they vary within these points on a scale of measurement or quality.

example.ex: They range in price from $3 to $15.
example.tran: 它们的价格从3美元到15美元不等。

example.ex: ...offering merchandise ranging from the everyday to the esoteric.
example.tran: 供应从日常用品到专业用具等各种商品

example.ex: ...temperatures ranging between 5℃ and 20℃.
example.tran: 温度变化在5℃到20℃之间

value.def: If a piece of writing or speech ranges over a group of topics, it includes all those topics.

example.ex: The conversation ranged over the desirability of such restaurants, the shortcomings of men, and why it had only taken 15 minutes to cross a continent.
example.tran: 谈话涉及了这类餐馆的吸引人之处、男人的弱点，还有为什么只用15分钟就跨越了一个大洲。

value.def: If people or things are ranged somewhere, they are arranged in a row or in lines.

example.ex: Some 300 trees have been ranged along the perimeter hedge...
example.tran: 沿着绿篱栽种着大约300棵树。

example.ex: More than 1,500 police and troops are ranged against them.
example.tran: 1,500多名警察和士兵列队与他们对峙。

value.def: If animals or people range somewhere, they move around in a place without having a particular destination in mind.

example.ex: Feeding is not a problem because the birds range over such a large area...
example.tran: 这种鸟活动的范围很大，因此觅食不成问题。

example.ex: They range widely in search of carrion.
example.tran: 它们在广阔的区域内搜寻腐肉。

value.def: A range of mountains or hills is a line of them.

example.ex: ...the massive mountain ranges to the north.
example.tran: 向北延伸的巨大山脉

example.ex: ...an impressive range of hills topped with trees.
example.tran: 山顶覆盖着树木的绵绵山峦

value.def: A range is a large area of open land, especially land in the United States where cattle are kept.
A rifle range or a shooting range is a place where people can practise shooting at targets.

example.ex: It reminds me of my days on the rifle range preparing for duty in Vietnam.
example.tran: 它使我想起了在靶场练习射击准备去越南服役的日子。

example.ex: ...an Army firing range.
example.tran: 陆军射击场

value.def: A range or kitchen range is an old-fashioned metal cooker.
A range or kitchen range is a large metal device for cooking food using gas or electricity. A range consists of a grill, an oven, and some gas or electric rings.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 cooker

value.def: If something is in range or within range, it is near enough to be reached or detected. If it is out of range, it is too far away to be reached or detected.

example.ex: Cars are driven through the mess, splashing everyone in range.
example.tran: 车从脏水里驶过，溅了周围所有人一身水。

example.ex: ...a base within range of enemy missiles...
example.tran: 在敌人导弹射程内的基地

example.ex: ...out of range of their rockets...
example.tran: 在他们火箭炮的射程之外

example.ex: The fish stayed 50 yards offshore, well out of range.
example.tran: 这种鱼生活在离岸50码的地方，完全钓不到。

value.tran: 在可及的范围内/在可及的范围外

value.def: If you see or hit something at close range or from close range, you are very close to it when you see it or hit it. If you do something at a range of half a mile, for example, you are half a mile away from it when you do it.

example.ex: He was shot in the head at close range...
example.tran: 他在近距离内被人用枪击中头部。

example.ex: McCoist knocked the ball in from close range.
example.tran: 麦克科伊斯特门前近距离将球攻入。

example.ex: ...photographing wild animals from close range...
example.tran: 对野生动物进行近距离拍摄

example.ex: The enemy opened fire at a range of only 20 yards.
example.tran: 敌人在距离仅20码的地方开火了。

value.tran: 接近地/靠近地/以…的距离

partsOfSpeech.dec: ar 加强 + range 行，列；顺序 → 成行 → 排列
arrange 安排；排列 + ment，arrange 的名词 → 排列，布置
de 毁 + range 行，列；顺序 → 破坏顺序 → 扰乱，引申为使精神错乱
dis 不 + arrange 安排；排列 → 不按顺序排列 → 弄乱
mis 错 + arrange 安排；排列 → 排列错误
re 重新 + arrange 安排；排列 → 重新安排
